r</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 5:41:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> As you know if you read the thread indicated in the subject line, I started a Dark Elf Warrior; all was going well, until I tried a quest by an NPC located at the guild house. You must give him your newbie sword and it spawns a 'Coward' NPC that you must kill and behead (without a weapon). Even though the NPC was /yellow, I was pretty much forced to continue this quest, and I (of course) lost miserably.<br>
<br>
I spawn without a sword, and going back to the NPC makes him act like it never happened.<br>
<br>
So I'm forced to start over, and I guess I'll try to level up a few times more before initiating that quest. Are there any quests that, if you fail, really screw you up? That is, in the mid- to end-game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uteiraa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teiraa</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Innoruuk also needs love</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 10:17:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/38/38498/pages/89050/teiraa3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> Sorry that you had this experience.<br>
Actually I'm rather careful with quests, and mostly ask other people before I start it, or check the websites (especially if the quest begins with giving away an important item). But there are a couple of nice quests, NPCs giving you a container to collect some items. Just keep that container! I still use a newbie quest container (made to collect beetle eyes) to store my necri words. <p><i><b>Teiraa Shadowflower</b> <br>
A Friendly Dark Elf Necromancer <br>
The Twilight Bastion<br>
@Firiona Vie <br></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udalninilvenorsh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalninil Venorsh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 10:45:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> Quests can be very harsh.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 548<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 11:55:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> While I agree that sucked, there must be a dark elf newbie warrior somewhere in town.  Pay them for their newbie sword, they can just die and get it back.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/6/02 3:59:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This particular quest ..</span><hr size=1> .. is typically only completed by twinks or with assistance.  You're a dark elf.  You're supposed to cheat. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 391<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/6/02 5:56:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> Couldn't you just get a rusty sword first, then turn in your newbie sword and kill the coward with the rusty? Still sucks if you turn in your sword unknowingly and lose it as described above, but it hardly seems you'd have to &quot;cheat&quot; to do the quest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farnoak>Farnoak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/6/02 11:19:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustration (sequel thread to starting stats)</span><hr size=1> There are quests that cost a ton of time and work if you fail them. Some epic quests require that you start over from scratch if you fail at a certain point. (I know the Rogue and Beastlord epic quests have points like this, I'm sure the others do as well.)<br>
<br>
Mainly screwing up a quest, at worst, just loses the main &quot;bottleneck&quot; item which you probably have to recamp.<br>
<br>
The biggest thing to watch out for when questing is faction. Some quests decrease factions you *really* don't want to decrease. Be very wary of quests that require you to kill mobs with bad factions tied to them. (Quests involving Kodal Fish and Mammoth..one of the bears of Surefall Glade...are most notable for royally messing up your factions with guild trainers.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/7/02 3:35:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Quest tip</span><hr size=1> Ah, yes, but with the &quot;science&quot; of the gnomes, one need not hurt any animal that has accidentally eaten something! The Regurgitonic, a creation of those mad scientists, er, &quot;skilled technologists&quot; in Ak'anon, is sufficient to recover a Koalindl Fish from everyone's dear friend, Frostbite, and I've heard that it can be used in Surefall Glade to get Mammoth to spit up some sort of list that some Qeynos citizen desires. By using your head, rather than brute force, you can complete these quests without losing any faction. (Not that that stops any of the truly violent from killing these poor animals, though.) Many quests for good characters that involve the murder of entities tied to other good factions can also be handled though alternate means, as well. Verant may be evil, but they're not *that* evil. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
All that's required is a Flask of Nitrates, conveniently available in Surefall Glade. Give it to the Zookeeper in Ak'anon to receive the Regurgitonic. <p>Illudin Arbitrator<br>
Enchanter and Incorrigible Adventurer<br>
Bringing together and calming Norrathians since 3174<br>
"Onward, all, to our destinies! Adventure awaits!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/7/02 11:29:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2250.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eh, &quot;cheat&quot; is relative</span><hr size=1> The NPC gives you terms to follow for the fight.  A true Teir'dal would ignore the terms and just kick the shit out of his opponent however he could.  This particular quest was a hot topic back in the day when everyone was under level 10.  IIRC, this was pretty much VI's response on it. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
